refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public boolReflectionProperty::isDynamic
Checks whether the property was declared at run-time, or whether the property was declared at compile-time.

&reftitle.returnvalues;

 &true; if the property was declared at run-time, or &false; if
 it was created at compile-time.

  &reftitle.examples;

   ReflectionProperty::isDynamic example


<?php

#[\AllowDynamicProperties]
class Foo {
    public $bar;
}

$o = new Foo();
$o->bar = 42;
$o->baz = 42;

$ro = new ReflectionObject($o);
var_dump($ro->getProperty('bar')->isDynamic());
var_dump($ro->getProperty('baz')->isDynamic());
?>


   &example.outputs;


bool(false)
bool(true)
